New tools for car expertise
In these days of bad weather and accidents, car garages are not the only winners.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered a disaster are brought back to a garage, where an expert has to assess the damage suffered and the cost of repair.
Each disaster is different, and the calculation of the cost of parts and labour time can be a long and complex work.
To calculate by hand the cost of a repair of between 20 000 and 30,000 euros, including parts and labor may take two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the assistance of the latest IT tools, it would be a matter of minutes.
That is why almost 100% of the experts use this type of system.
Service providers and solutions for disaster assessment and maintenance are dedicated to the collection of information provided by manufacturers, and then to process them and offer them to their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, of the North American group Solera, is the leading company; 80% of the estimates are made with its products.
The other companies competing in the field of evaluation tools and the development of information on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with data provided by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Commercial Director of Audatex, the company in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides them with information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed continues to increase, so that over the last five years more versions, variants and motorizations have been launched than in the previous fifteen years.
When a new car goes out on the market, these companies get to work.
This is a very hard work, as each of the thousand parts of the vehicle must be catalogued and the price entered.
In addition, a "intelligent" graphic image of each model is established on which you can click on the different parts of a tourist car.
If it is a model sold massively, work can be ready within a week if the process progresses very quickly.
If it's a cheap car, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information about 99.2% of the cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models, for example, they have information about the Porsche, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini.
For vehicles in circulation, the figure exceeds 99 %.
In order to carry out the work of documentation and database development, Audatex has eight centres distributed worldwide (in Spain, France, Germany, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each is specialized in certain brands.
The national seat is located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than one hundred technicians (generally mechanical experts) work simultaneously on three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million per year to develop these databases.
Each month, 2.5 million data are recorded, and customers receive updates every two days.
The development of this huge flow of information enables these companies to offer different uses and various products.
The most common application concerns repair and maintenance, but depending on the countries, there are also tools for the management of broken parts or for the calculation of the venal or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide that informs about the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not propose it in our country, but it does so in the United States.
In view of the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support it can provide to industry professionals.
This company offers ten different tools, the lighthouse product being AudaPlus, the standard solution for assessing claims, for experts.
These include cars, motorcycles, light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it takes into account the repair time estimated by the manufacturer or the painting scales.
This tool is purchased according to its use, for each estimate.
The highest cost is 5.75 euros, for customers who use it little, up to ten times a month.
Then, each insurance company, which carries out thousands of expertise, negotiates its price with Audatex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the total identification of a vehicle and equipment with which it came out of the assembly chain only through its chassis number.
AudaGlass focuses on vehicle lenses, and AudaSubastas is an open-source server to the professional sector on the Internet that allows to hit broken vehicles.
Its statistical service is very useful to identify trends, perform geo-demographic analyses or know the current problems by brand or model.
It is possible to study, for example, how many models of a specified trademark have gone to the garage for a failure or how many have suffered severe losses for a given period.
Gt Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of such tools.
It sells, among other things, Gt Estimante, which is also intended for experts and provides digital images, as well as access to the manufacturer's official parts, prices and time.
Gt Motive is a company of the Einsa group, founded in 1971, as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of claims, failures or maintenance of motor vehicles.
